    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.21/244.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Colombian Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I beg you to accept my thanks
                    for your very kind letter of the 9th instant congratulating me on the signature
                    of the convention between the United States and Colombia.</p>
                <p>While it would seem that the convention is not all that you would wish, I feel
                    confident that you will share with me in the hope that <pb facs="0278" n="162"
                        xml:id="pg_162"/> it will result in the removal of all friction between the
                    two Governments and in the restoration of their ancient cordial friendship.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
